OL,3,CWhen will the Pink Moon appear and how
OL,4,Cdoes it get its name?
OL,6,FEaster falls each year on the Sunday
OL,7,Fafter the first full Moon following
OL,8,Fspring equinox - that's April 5 this
OL,9,Fyear.
OL,11,FWhen can I see the Pink Moon?
OL,13,FKeen star gazers will have to wait up
OL,14,Flate, or get up very early to see the
OL,15,FPink Moon at its best, with the most
OL,16,Fbrilliant point of its cycle happening
OL,17,Fat 3.12am on Thursday.
OL,19,FGenerally the Pink Moon can be seen
OL,20,Ffrom anywhere in the UK, however,
OL,21,Fvisibility is weather dependent.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
